reviewText: I received an early release last week, and my son (3 1/2) has been absolutely fascinated. He asks for this DVD every time he gets to pick a show to watch, and he would watch it on continuous repeat if we'd let him. It's not as annoying as some of the other shows he likes, and there is very little commercialism in this DVD - a surprise, considering there is a Christmas episode. They don't even force viewers to fast-forward past a bunch of previews to get to the menu. The focus is really on the rescues, problem solving, and the friendships between the team members. I wish there were more than one female in the team and she didn't wear pink, but that's a minor quibble.

My son loves "Paw Patrol" so I wanted to know what was going to be on this DVD.  Since there isn't a description of what this DVD is yet, I am posting this review to include the description I found elsewhere on the Internet.  I wanted to know, so thought others would too, in order to make a decision whether to buy or not.  Here's the description from http://paw-patrol.wikia.com

"PAW Patrol" is on a roll - even through the ice and snow - in these 7 wintery missions, including a double-length adventure to save Christmas! From a ski-lift rescue to tracking down a snow monster, no job is too big and no pup is too small. Plus, see how Rubble first joined the team by helping out in a snowy situation.

Episodes:
Pups Save Christmas
Pups Get a Rubble
Pups and the Snow Monster
Pups Get a Lift
Pups on Ice
Pups Save the Treats
Pups Fall Festival

I gave it 5 stars because we have seen some of the episodes already on TV, so we already know we like them.  I do wish, however, that they would include more episodes per DVD.

My son is currently obsessed with Paw Patrol anything. I had gotten him a different Paw Patrol movie, but he was getting bored with it. He decided that Chase and Marshall are his favorite of the pups, so what better than to get him a movie mainly focused on these two?! I love that it auto-plays, because it gives me a change to get some homework or cleaning done, with limitations of course, and that it has more than just one or two episodes. This movie is perfect for any child that is obsessed with Paw Patrol. I'll be ordering another one here soon as a back up for when this one gets broken, which can easily happen with a rambunctious 3 year old!
Great thing about this is that it keeps playing after all the cartoons are done.  It just restarts again.  Keeps a 2 year old very happy.

Another wonderful addition to the growing library of children's cartoon DVDs!  Like so many kiddos out there, mine are currently in love with Paw Patrol.  I actually think the show is pretty cute and entertaining too, so I don't mind putting this on in the car when we're on long road trips.  Marshall, Skye, Chase, Rubble, Everest, Rocky, Zuma and Ryder help pass the time and entertain the kids in the back.

This is a group of episodes all relating to snow, ice, and cold weather.  Luckily, that means there's a lot of Everest!  She's one of our favs and it's nice to see her on the screen.

This is a great length to pop in for a road trip.  We can watch several episodes between necessary pit stops.  I love that episodes are only 11 minutes long...it makes it easy to watch a quick one when you only have a little bit of time.

I'd highly recommend this DVD.  It's a great price.  Kids LOVE Paw Patrol.  It's a goofy, wholesome show that I have zero problems letting my kids enjoy.  A+!
